The paper focuses on analyzing the performance and scalability of Distributed Deep Neural Networks, which falls under the categories of Distributed Computing (cs.DC), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper specifically mentions the use of CNTK, which is a popular deep learning framework, further supporting the relevance to these categories.
